## Changes

### `src/unison/pipeline.py` (committed in `0cc208c`)
- Added `import threading`
- Added `self.cancel_event = threading.Event()` to `DAGScheduler.__init__` — a cooperative cancellation flag
- In `execute_parallel`: clears the event at start (`self.cancel_event.clear()`), sets it (`self.cancel_event.set()`) when any stage exceeds its deadline
- Updated docstring to document the cancel_event behavior

### `src/unison/orchestrator.py` (committed in `0cc208c`)
- `_run_dag_development` captures `scheduler.cancel_event` via closure
- `exec_stage` checks `cancel_event.is_set()` before invoking agents — returns `False` early when cancellation has been signaled

### `ARCHITECTURE.md` (committed in `0cc208c`)
- Added **DAG Mode (Experimental)** section documenting cooperative cancellation, known limitations (Python can't kill threads, best-effort failure propagation, one agent per stage), and recommending the stable sequential loop for production use

### `tests/test_pipeline.py`
- 4 new tests: `test_cancel_event_not_set_on_normal_execution`, `test_cancel_event_set_on_timeout`, `test_cancel_event_cleared_between_calls`, `test_executor_observes_cancel_event`


